			<div class="content" id="post-content-2241997">
									

<p>I thought this was fantastic.</p>
<p>The hidden text adds a lot, though I'm not totally sure it <em>should</em> be hidden; I wish I'd read this once through without the hidden text so I'd be able to give a better opinion on that.</p>
<p>Solace is a very compelling character. I find this almost surprising, given that this stemmed from a silly joke, and is partially based on an anomalous character trait a million and one newbies have tried (and failed) to pull off.</p>
<p>It partly works because of the really nice writing (a lot of good lines in here). It also works because you play a lot of it fairly straight-faced; if you'd tried to go goofier, it wouldn't have worked.</p>
<p>I enjoyed the usage of previously established characters as well (and not <em>just</em> the expected ones). Made this character and story feel like they fit into a larger universe.</p>

							</div>

								
